# 📌 Project Scope – SmartSplit

## 🧠 Project Overview

**SmartSplit** is a full-stack expense-sharing and budgeting web application. It helps users split bills with friends or groups, track shared expenses, upload receipts, and get AI-powered suggestions to better manage their budget. Built with React, NestJS, PostgreSQL, Docker, and AWS.

---

## 🎯 Project Goals

- Learn and demonstrate real-world experience with:
  - Node.js (NestJS)
  - React with TypeScript
  - PostgreSQL with Prisma ORM
  - Docker for containerization
  - AWS for database and file storage
- Build a clean, well-structured project to showcase on GitHub 
- Apply best practices in backend API design, frontend development, and DevOps

---

## ✨ Core Features

### ✅ Authentication
- User registration and login with JWT
- Password hashing and secure token storage

### ✅ Expense Sharing
- Create and join expense groups (e.g., "Trip to Melbourne")
- Add and split expenses with group members
- Automatically calculate balances (who owes whom)

### ✅ Dashboard
- View personal and group balances
- Visual summaries of spending
- Charts for spending categories (e.g., rent, food, travel)

### ✅ File Upload (AWS S3)
- Upload receipts or expense proofs
- Securely store files in AWS S3 bucket

### ✅ AI Suggestions (Optional Bonus)
- Use OpenAI or AWS Bedrock to analyze expense history
- Provide smart tips: e.g., "You spent 40% more than last month on food"

---

## 🧪 Technical Goals

- Master modular architecture with NestJS
- Write clean, typed backend code using TypeScript
- Implement Docker + Docker Compose for dev and deployment
- Integrate AWS services: RDS (PostgreSQL), S3
- Use GitHub Actions for CI/CD pipeline (optional)

---

## 🔜 Stretch Goals

- Real-time updates with WebSocket (for group chats or live expense updates)
- Multi-currency support with automatic exchange rates
- Admin dashboard to manage groups and users

